  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Health and Nutrition Response for drought and conflicted-affected IDP and Vulnerable Host communities in Herat and Badghis Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project responds to the gaps in access to lifesaving health and nutrition services among approximately 200,000 new IDPs scattered across 9 IDP sites in Herat as well as 120,000 IDPs in Badghis. The project will also increase the availability of health and Nutrition services through supporting Static Referral Hospitals in Herat (Herat PD Hospital) to provide nutrition services. To achieve this, WV will take over 7 Mobile Integrated Health and Nutrition teams in Herat and Badghis IDP sites. These teams are currently being run by UNICEF and DoPH and will be transitioned to WV starting 1 January 2019. Further, WV will recruit 4 Doctors and 3 Nutrition nurses who will be seconded to Herat PD hospital and other referral hospitals in Herat as well as the other Referal centers around IDP sites. WV will also provide a 24 Hr Ambulance service in IDP sites in Herat. WV will also recruit a team of well-experienced health and nutrition personnel who will be a mobile supportive supervision team assisting MHNTs in service provision</narrative>
  </description>
